text: Wasilla is a small city in the U.S. state of Alaska, about 43 miles from Anchorage. It is one of the ten largest cities in Alaska. Sarah Palin was once mayor and owns a house with her family there. The city's population was 9,054 at the 2020 census. ==References== ==Other websites== *Official City of Wasilla website Category:Cities in Alaska
title: Wasilla, Alaska
